---
name: perf
description: Check bundle size and run Lighthouse performance audit
user-invocable: true
allowed-tools:
  - Bash(npm run build *)
  - Bash(npm run *)
  - Bash(pnpm run build *)
  - Bash(pnpm run *)
  - Bash(npx *)
  - Bash(du *)
  - Bash(ls *)
  - Bash(cat *)
  - Read
  - Glob
---

Run a performance check on the project:

1. Build the project (`npm run build` or equivalent from CLAUDE.md).
2. Report bundle size:
   - List files in the build output directory with sizes
   - Highlight the largest files and total size
   - Compare to previous build if stats are available
3. If the project is a web app, run Lighthouse CI:
   - `npx lighthouse-ci --collect.staticDistDir=<build-dir>` or equivalent
   - Report key scores: Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices, SEO
4. Flag any concerns:
   - Bundle files over 250KB (gzipped)
   - Lighthouse performance score under 90
   - Large unminified assets
5. Suggest specific improvements if issues are found.
